{{Infobox book | name = The Republican Brain: The Science of Why They Deny Science — and Reality | image = The Republican Brain (book cover).jpg | caption = | author = [[Chris Mooney (journalist)|Chris Mooney]] | country = United States | language = English | series = | subjects = [[Conservatism in the United States]], [[Republican Party (United States)]], [[Antiscience]] | publisher = Wiley | release_date = 2012 | media_type = Print | pages = 327 | isbn = 9781118094518 | oclc = 773429781 | followed_by = }}
'''''The Republican Brain: The Science of Why They Deny Science — and Reality ''''' is a 2012 book about the [[Psychology|psychological basis]] for many [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans']] rejection of [[Science|mainstream scientific]] theories, as well as theories of [[economics]] and [[history]], by the journalist [[Chris Mooney (journalist)|Chris Mooney]].
==Reception== The ''[[Financial Times]]'' gave the book a favorable review, describing it as an "intelligent, nuanced and persuasive account" of psychological differences in political behavior.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/d690e4ba-8a13-11e1-a0c8-00144feab49a.html#axzz1zeNQ4IS9 |title=Political animals |first= James |last= Wilsdon |date= 28 April 2012 |newspaper=[[Financial Times]] |accessdate= 2012-07-03}}</ref>
[[Alissa Quart]], in a ''[[New York Times]]'' opinion piece, cited conservative writers Alex Berezow and Hank Campbell who equated Mooney's argument with [[eugenics]].<ref name= "Quart">{{cite news |last= Quart |first= Alissa |authorlink= Alissa Quart |date= 23 November 2012 |title= Neuroscience: Under attack |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/25/opinion/sunday/neuroscience-under-attack.html |newspaper= [[The New York Times]] |accessdate= 2014-04-24}}</ref><ref name= "Berezow">{{cite news |last= Berezow |first= Alex |date= 26 April 2012 |title= Are Republicans genetically inferior to Democrats? |url= http://www.realclearbooks.com/articles/2012/04/26/are_republicans_genetically_inferior_12.html |accessdate= 2016-03-19}}</ref> It was criticized by [[Conservatism in the United States|American conservative]] [[Jonah Goldberg]],<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/opinion/forum/story/2012-05-01/republicans-brain-science-democrats/54647948/1 |newspaper= [[USA Today]] |type= Column |title= Republicans have bad brains? |authorlink=Jonah Goldberg |last= Goldberg |first= Jonah | date= 30 April 2012}}</ref> who tried to associate it with "conservative [[phrenology]]". Mooney responded, stating that Goldberg had mispresented his book in several respects.<ref name="MooneyRespondsToGoldberg"/> Mooney also stated that Goldberg exhibited "precisely the traits he seeks to deny: ideological defensiveness, a lack of nuance, and a deeply unwarranted and overconfident sense of certainty".<ref name="MooneyRespondsToGoldberg">{{cite news |url= http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/opinion/letters/story/2012-05-03/chirs-mooney-republican-brain/54733296/1 |newspaper= [[USA Today]] |department= Letters | title= Goldberg misunderstands ''Republican Brain'' |first= Chris |last= Mooney |authorlink= Chris Mooney (journalist) |date= 3 May 2012}}</ref> Mooney later rebutted a similar criticism by [[Andrew Ferguson]] and stated that Ferguson dismissed science himself while attacking the book.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://scienceprogressaction.org/intersection/2012/05/the-weekly-standard-slam-the-republican-brain/ | work=[[Science Progress]] | title= ''The Weekly Standard'' slams ''The Republican Brain'' |first= Chris |last= Mooney |authorlink= Chris Mooney (journalist) |date= 14 May 2012}}</ref>
[[Paul Krugman]] wrote in ''The New York Times'' that Mooney makes a good point: the [[Trait theory|personality traits]] associated with modern conservatism, particularly a lack of [[openness]], make the modern Republican Party hostile to the idea of [[Objectivity (philosophy)|objective]] [[inquiry]].<ref>{{cite news |last= Krugman |first= Paul |authorlink= Paul Krugman |date= 19 November 2012 |newspaper= [[The New York Times]] |title= Views differ on age of planet |url= http://nyti.ms/1lHEaiz |accessdate= 2014-04-24}}</ref>
