==Judaic hermeneutics==
{{Main|Talmudical hermeneutics}}

'''Talmudical Hermeneutics''' ([[Hebrew]]:  approximately, '''מידות שהתורה נדרשת בהן''') is the science which defines the rules and methods for the investigation and exact determination of the meaning of the [[Tanakh|Scriptures]], both legal and historical. Since the [[Halakah]], however, is regarded simply as an exposition and explanation of the [[Torah]], [[Talmud]] [[hermeneutics]] includes also the rules by which the requirements of the oral law are derived from and established by the written law.

==Islamic hermeneutics==
{{Main|Qur'anic hermeneutics}}

'''Qur'anic hermeneutics''' is the study of theories of the interpretation and understanding of the [[Qur'an]], the [[Muslim]] holy book. Throughout religious history, Qur'anic scholars have sought to mine the wealth of its meanings by developing a variety of different systems of [[hermeneutics]].

